The issue is that `electron` (which is in devDependencies) has a huge `node_modules/electron/dist/` folder with all the electron source code. And `@electron/packager` has 70+ MB of its own files.

Instead of trying to ignore everything, let me just run `npm install --production` to install only the production dependencies (those in `dependencies`, not `devDependencies`). This is the cleanest solution.
</think>

